name.text:
Dose 1 to dose 2 interval 6 months-4 days.  Series complete. 
Evaluation_Test_Type: Interval: At Absolute Minimum
General_Description: This test case describes when a second dose of the Hep A 2 dose vaccine is administered to a child at 18 months age and with an interval of at least 6 months -4 days after the previous dose, that the dose is considered valid and no additional doses are recommended.  The series is complete.
